The Inspector-General of Police, IGP Mohammed Adamu Friday  described the Kubwa NYSC Orientation camp as heavily looted and promised that  it is working hard to round up the perpetrators.  Our correspondent Nathan Williams reports that the Police boss who said this today in Kubwa Abuja after an on the spot assessment of the looted and vandalized NYSC camp noted that so far 53 persons have been arrested so far for looting the camp and some of the items recovered.  The Director General of the National Youth Service Corps, Brigadier General Shuaibu Ibrahim, says palliatives are not stored in any of their camps across the country. Ibrahim, who said they were preparing for the camp to be reopened on November 10, 2020, begged Nigerians not to attack their facilities. 